item.title: .Vroom
item.dc:creator: @xxlegitxx xxlegitxx
item.description:
@xxlegitxx wrote:

Alexia, I don’t understand you.

Though it’s been mentioned, why post a sig when you’ve only spent 13 minutes on it? Why post a sig at all if you don’t give a crap what anyone thinks of you? By posting a sig, you want recognition. By putting the fact that you spent 13 minutes on it, then want to shift the recognition in the positive direction, hence lending towards the fact that you indeed care what other people think of you.

Furthermore, it looks complete. It’s not like you were in the middle of making it and found something better to do. It was planned. You finished, then found something better to do. Two things could have happened. You set a timer and said, I’m bored, so I’ll occupy myself for 13 minutes, no more no less. Or, you actually spent more than 13 minutes and completed the sig, decided it looked shitty, and put that you spent 13 minutes on it so people would use that as a standard. I find the latter more likely.

And finally, if you don’t care what people think of you, why would you pass images of this other chick as yourself in the post your picture thread?

Read full topic
